<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-577-884  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 577 884.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Robotics and Automation  June 1989 v5 n3p362(7).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Analysis and design of a modular electrooptical tactile sensor.andO;(technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ristic, R.; Benhabib, B.; Goldenberg, A.A.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A prototype modular tactile sensor is developed that uses opticalfibers in an electro optical system to measure the amount of forceat a single point and in a four-point array.andP;  Touch feedback isexpected to be employed more and more in automated systems,particularly in robot manipulators.andP;  The new electrooptical systemmeasures the amplitude of a light emitted from an optical fiber asit is reflected off the inner surface of a beam assembly that isdeflected from an applied force.andP;  The amount of light received bya second fiber is correlated to a degree of force.andP;  Advantages ofthe system include freedom from electromagnetic interference,safety in hazardous environments, passive operation, andelectrical isolation.andP;  The prototype system validates thetechnology's effectiveness for industrial implementation.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     PrototypeFiber OpticsRobot ArmsSystem DevelopmentOptoelectronic DevicesSensorsTouch Sensors.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   The RAL force sensor prototype schematic. (chart)Schematic of the prototype force sensor setup. (chart)Schematic of light path inside sensor. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>